[[!meta title="Canned Coffee — UCC Kuro No Yo-in"]]
[[!tag Canned_Coffee Review]]

UCC BLACK 「黒の余韻」 _Kuro no yo-in_ is a new vocabulary word for me.
Literally _UCC BLACK Dark Aftertaste_. 余韻 _yo-in_ describes the finish of a
drink or musical chord. Though poetic in its typical use, the employment of the
phrase _kuro no yo-in_ to describe this canned coffee in particular is far less
subtle than normal. Even in English underneath the Japanese description it says
「FULL BODIED BITTERNESS」. And that description is damn accurate.

<figure>
[[!template id="hooya-img.tmpl" cid="bafkreigikuuvi4p7n4vebblhyfz7tpwow6rrhrzdnw7d2ghit4t3tyde3q" size=medium]]
</figure>

This UCC twist-top is bitter and unforgiving. With no added sugar or salt, UCC
makes no attempt to mask its taste. Dark, deep and beautifully minimal. It's
literally just coffee in an aluminum can. It tastes as bitter as a cigarette
butt. That's all to say: this coffee is awesome. Canned with a resealable cap if
you're not drinking it all in one go, it is able to be served hot or chilled.

